From ccabec064092d75f8ec59e821139d5b1c3e28a74 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: MedPath Dev <dev@medpath.in>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 05:50:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add modular MedPath landing page with blurred-lab hero
 background

- New standalone MedpathLandingComponent (features/medpath-landing/)
  with its own .ts/.html/.css, kept fully separate from the existing
  LisLandingComponent (features/lis-home) and legacy LandingComponent
  (features/landing) so nothing already shipped is touched.
- Hero visual panel now renders a soft, heavily-blurred SVG illustration
  of a lab bench, test-tube rack, and microscope behind the operator
  login card (filter: blur(26px), opacity .4) plus a colour-wash and
  reduced-motion fallback, so the card stays the clear focal point.
- Reuses global design tokens from src/styles.css (--card-bg,
  --border-color, --text-primary/secondary, --body-bg, --font-family,
  --primary, --primary-dark, --accent-light) via component-scoped
  aliases, so the page follows whichever theme palette is active.
- Registered on a new, non-breaking route: /landing-preview.
  The default '/' -> 'lis-home' redirect is untouched.
